@KevvoLightswift yes, it’s still slop.  People whose brains have been turned to mush can love slop, it’s still slop.  Avatar was like the highest-grossing movie ever (not-adjusted) and it was slop.

The standards these critics have are neither “niche” nor “specified”.  That is such a stupid take I doubt you actually understand what those words mean.  We just have basic STANDARDS.  If Minecraft came out just 10-15 years ago it would have been universally panned because people wouldn’t have been served an endless parade of movies that are so lacking in basic structure and storytelling that this movie NOT being quite as OBVIOUS broken wouldn’t be seen as “Well, that’s ok then!”

Everyone who likes this slop movie keeps saying that what they liked were the “jokes” and the “references”.  People were acting like actual hooligans and destroying theaters because the actor said… “chicken jockey”.  That’s… that’s all it is, an endless procession of references.  That’s not a movie.  That’s just digitized slop.  There are literally dozens of DCOMs that beat this slop just because they actually have basic plot structure.  DCOMs.

